{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce VAT for Hospitality and Small Business to 5% indefinitely.",
        "additional_details": "We petition the Government and Parliament to reduce VAT in the hospitality industry and small businesses to 5%. The current 20% rate imposes a heavy burden, hindering growth and job creation. By lowering VAT, businesses can invest, retain employees, and improve services. This reduction is crucial for recovery from the COVID-19 pandemic, stimulating economic activity and attracting tourists. Many countries have adopted reduced VAT rates for hospitality, providing a competitive edge. We urge the Government to conduct an economic impact assessment to evaluate the potential benefits. Lowering VAT to 5% will support businesses, foster innovation, and strengthen communities. Let us join together to create a thriving and sustainable economy.",
        "background": "Petition for reduced VAT in hospitality and small businesses to 5%. Urging the Government and Parliament to alleviate financial burden, stimulate growth, and aid recovery from COVID-19. Reduce VAT to 5% to support businesses, retain jobs, and attract tourism.",
